sentences: Jimmy Fortune (born March 11, 1955) is an American country music singer from Nelson County, Virginia.
Fortune started performing with the Statler Brothers in 1982, and joined the group permanently later in the year when DeWitt was unable to return to the stage.
In 2002, Don, Harold and Phil of the Statler Brothers retired.
In 2015 he released Hits & Hymns produced by Ben Isaacs.
Fortune sang tenor for The Statler Brothers for 21 years, and wrote the song "Elizabeth" for the group.
